(96, 6, 'Text Completion - Text 2', '<p>Profit Up In (1)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; Sector<br />\r\n<br />\r\nGalaxy Systems reported a fourth quarter profit of $250,000, compared (2)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; a loss of nearly $2 million during the same period last year. This was the first quarter with a profit for the computer company, which began operations five years ago.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAccording to the year-end report form Goldboro, Inc., the company&rsquo;s profit rose 20%. The rise in profits is attributed to the introduction of a new software system for personal finance accounting. The company hopes to further increase its (3)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; next year by expanding its markets overseas.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Providence has been losing a significant portion of its market share to competitors, but the company is optimistic about the future. &ldquo;We&rsquo;re confident that our plans for bringing more efficient and less (4)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; wireless service to our customer will result in increased market share and greater profits than the company has ever enjoyed in the past&rdquo; said Thomas P. Witherspoon, CEO.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(97, 6, 'Text Completion - Text 3', '<p><strong>BOURNESVILLE BANK</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIs pleased to announce the opening of a new branch at 1109 South Boulevard in the Green Lake section of town.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis (1)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; a full-service branch where you can be sure of receiving the professional, prompt, and friendly service that you are accustomed to at all Bournesville Bank branches.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nPlease join us for the grand opening of our new branch on Monday, May 22 during our regular business hours 9:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.<br />\r\nThere will be refreshments, live (2)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;, and prizes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBank staff will be on hand to explain all the service available to our customers. Everyone who opens a new (3)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; during the Gran opening will receive a special bonus gift.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis gift is our way of saying &ldquo;thank you&rdquo; for doing business with us.<br />\r\nBournesville Bank, your partner in all your business and personal (4)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; needs.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(98, 6, 'Text Completion - Text 4', '<p>To: All personal<br />\r\nFrom: Marina, Director<br />\r\nRe: Travel expenses<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are all aware that the procedures for charging and reporting expenses for business trips taken on behalf of the company have long been out of land. As a result (1)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; recommendations from the Budget Office, the following procedures will be adopted.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nCompany personnel will no longer be given company credit cards to cover expenses while on out of town trips. Instead, all travel expenses, with the (2)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; of airline tickets which will continue to be charged directly to the company, will be paid for out of pocket. In order to receive (3)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; an expense report must be submitted to your department head within ten days of returning from a trip. All charges must be itemized on the report and accompanied by receipts. Approval of each item will be made at the discretion of each department head, following of course, the company expense guidelines (see attached).<br />\r\n<br />\r\nGenerally, charges for hotels, meals, and transportation will be (4)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;. Non-work related items such as entertainment, excessive taxi rides, and bar bills will not. I am sure you will all understand the necessity of this strict attitude toward expense reporting. I am counting on everyone&rsquo;s cooperation.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(99, 6, 'Text Completion - Text 5', '<p>April 17<br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo whom it may concern:<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThis letter is (1)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; for Mr. Young Kim, who has worked for this company as an administrative assistant for the past three years.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDuring most of his time here, Mr. Kim has worked directly under (2)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; supervision. He has served as an assistant to a busy accounting office with a staff of five. He (3)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; himself to be reliable and hardworking. He has never shirked his duties, even when the office workload has required him to work late into the evening or on a weekend. I always feel sure that whatever task I may give him, it will be done promptly and with a smile. Mr. Kim&rsquo;s friendliness and upbeat attitude have been a real contribution to the office environment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe will miss Mr. Kim, but we understand that he is ready to move on to a (4)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; that will make better use of his skills and provide him with more opportunities for his future. I can recommend him without reservation and know he will make a great contribution to any work environment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSincerely,<br />\r\nIvan Sokolow</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(100, 6, 'Text Completion - Text 6', '<p><strong>The National Museum of Art</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIs proud to announce the upcoming (1)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; of European Expressionist paintings and prints, from January 15 through March 15.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nWe are very fortunate to be able to bring this opportunity to area residents and visitors. This show includes works on loan from museums and collectors all around the world. It is the first time this area has been (2)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; wide representation of Expressionist works together in one place<br />\r\n.<br />\r\n(3)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; for the shows are available by calling the museum&rsquo;s Special Events office at 342 555 0980.<br />\r\nDuring the show, the Museum Gift Store (4)&hellip;&hellip;&hellip; on sale catalogues, art reproduction, calendars, coffee mugs, and other souvenirs of the show.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(101, 7, 'Single Passage - Text 1', '<p>Those old Movie Goer magazines in the basement may be worth more than you would imagine. A 152 copy featuring Clark Gable can be worth over $750 and an old Lucille Ball is valued at $900. But it&rsquo;s not just the oldies that are worth so much money. A collection of twenty-five Lost in Space covers form June, 2001 sells for more than $450 online. &ldquo;The internet has been great for collecting and has made it a lot easier to find things&rdquo;, says George Boulis, 58, a Boston based collector who has all the Movie Goer Magazine covers. They&rsquo;re worth about $28000. And what do you think is the most valuable issue? The first one, of course: a mint-condition copy goes for more than $1850.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(102, 7, 'Single Passage - Text 2', '<p><strong>Miami-Dade County Transit Authority<br />\r\nLANE CLOSURES</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nDue to continued construction on Interstate 95, the two left lanes on the north side will be closed from NE 78<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;St. to NE 135<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;St between the hours of midnight and 6:00 A.M. Monday to Friday, and 10:00 P.M. to 7 A.M. weekends.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nLane closures are scheduled to begin on October 16 and continue until November 6.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We regret any inconvenience to motorists.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(103, 7, 'Single Passage - Text 3', '<p><strong>MEMORANDUM</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nTo: All Atlantis Corporation Employees<br />\r\nFrom: Myrtle Sternbridge, Chief Financial Officer<br />\r\nRe: Two-day unpaid leave<br />\r\nDate: June 3<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt is my unhappy duty to inform you that the Board of Directors has voted to impose a two-day layoff for all employees in order to avoid an operating budget shortfall.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe company is facing a serious crisis due to poor profits over the past two quarters. The budget is short by about $13 million and according to our bylaw, the budget must be balanced by June 30, the end of this fiscal year.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nIt is necessary for all employees to give up&nbsp; two days&rsquo; pay in order to put an end to the budget crisis. Employees are to speak to their supervisors regarding scheduling the two days that they are not to report to work.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAccording to the agreement reached between Atlantis Corp. and the union, employees will be reimbursed for the days they lose during the first six months of the next fiscal year if profits improve.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nI sincerely regret the need to take such drastic measures to end the current budget crisis, but with your cooperation, we can see this through.</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
(104, 7, 'Single Passage - Text 4', '<p>LONDON &ndash; In May, Great Britain&rsquo;s Home Office, deciding on compensation for a man who served four years in prison for industrial espionage that he did not commit, ruled that he was entitled to about $1.1 million. They sais, however, that he would have to reimburse the prison about $23.000 for four years&rsquo; room and board. The outraged Michael O&rsquo;Brien, age 34, was freed by a Court of Appeal. He said, &ldquo;They don&rsquo;t charge guilty people for bed and board. They only charge innocent people!&rdquo;</p>\r\n', NULL, NULL),
